\describe{
\item{\code{~ a | b}}{First split the plot horizontally by \code{a}
(columns whose widths reflect marginal proportions of \code{a}).
Then, within each column, split vertically by \code{b} (rows whose
heights reflect conditional proportions of \code{b} given \code{a}).
This is the classic two-variable marimekko / mosaic plot.}
\item{\code{~ a | b | c}}{Horizontal by \code{a}, then vertical by \code{b},
then horizontal again by \code{c}. Three levels of nesting with
alternating directions (h \eqn{\to} v \eqn{\to} h).}
\item{\code{~ a + b | c}}{Horizontal by \code{a}, then horizontal again
by \code{b} (same direction because \code{+} groups them), then vertical
